. For instance} 16. Bxd5 Qxd5 17. Qxd5 cxd5 18. Bxe5 f6 19. Bf4 Kf7 20. Rfd1 {.}) 16. Rc1 Qa5 17. Rxc6 {. To further illustrate:} Qxa2 $4 18. Qh5 h6 19. Rxe6 fxe6 20. Qxe5 Bf6 21. Qxe6+ Kh8 22. Qf5 Kg8 23. Qh7+ Kf7 24. Re1) 15. Qc2 Nd7 {Black must walk on this very narrow path to survive. Now both} 16. Nd2 ({and} 16. Qxc6 {should promise White a small edge.}) *

