nal is cleared. This means Black will have to spend a few tempi before he can complete his development.}) 12. Re1 {White has several ways to approach this position: One idea is to target the c5 -pawn with Ba3 . This plan forces Black to weaken the a8 - h1 diagonal. The second way is a bit more aggressive: placing the knight on e3 .} *

