1. e4 c5 2. b3 Nc6 3. Bb2 d5 {It is too early for this move, and the downside can be seen at first glance: Black's queen has to enter the game at a very early stage and lose a tempo.} 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nc3 Qe6+ {This is not a good square to give check. True, the queen managed to get out of the range of the g1 -knight. However, now the c8 -bishop is blocked in.} 6. Be2 Nf6 7. Nf3 {It has become apparent that Black has to spend one more tempo with the queen.} g6 ({The correct way to play would be} 7... Qd7 {, when play can continue as follows:} 8. O-O e6 9. Re1 Be7 10. Bb5 $1 Qc7 11. Ne5 Bd7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. Qf3 Rc8 14. Ne4 {White already has several threats while Black is struggling to complete development. This is a logical outcome, as Black spent four moves with her majesty!}) 8. Nb5 Qd7 9. Ne5 Qd8 10. Bc4 {This position needs no comment!} *

